In the end, of all and nothing
After time, and before space
In the infinite and of all and none
They sat in a heavy flat-bottomed boat, each holding a long,
crooked rod in his hands and eagerly waiting for "a bite."
The line was silent for so long that she checked her phone to see
if the call had been dropped.
How long are you going to put up with this?

In 2005, Halton Borough Council put up a notice to tell the public about its
plans to move a path from one place to another. Quite astonishingly,
the notice was a 630 word sentence, which picked up one of our Golden Bull
awards that year. Here is it in full.

